'''Giuseppe Caracciolo''' was an Italian [[cinematographer]], who worked on more than forty films during his career which stretched from the [[silent era]] into the Post-[[Second World War|War]] years. In 1944, he was employed on [[Vittorio De Sica]]'s ''[[The Children Are Watching Us]]''.<ref>Cardullo p.87</ref>

==Selected filmography==
* ''[[Sun (film)|Sun]]'' (1929)
* ''[[The White Ship (1941 film)|The White Ship]]'' (1941)
* ''[[Men on the Sea Floor]]'' (1941)
* ''[[Giarabub (film)|Giarabub]]'' (1942)
* ''[[The Children Are Watching Us]]'' (1944)
* ''[[The Tyrant of Padua]]'' (1946)
* ''[[The Emperor of Capri]]'' (1949)
* ''[[Toto Looks For a House]]'' (1949)
* ''[[Red Moon (1951 film)|Red Moon]]'' (1951)

